issues.body:
// originally from josselin=40life360.com@dmarc.ietf.org on May 11th, 2023
// via unwanted-trackers@ietf.org

3: Advertising Interval

The advertising Interval requirements in 3.9:

There is no justification to constraint devices to these advertising intervals so the requirement should be removed.

// to: draft-detecting-unwanted-location-trackers@ietf.org
// from: <klein.elliot@gmail.com> 
// on: May 2, 2023


I recommend the addition of "Shipment/Package" as one additional category to list as I anticipate devices included on or within package shipments will help monitor if lost or otherwise to determine ETA or other exceptions to on-time delivery of important packages -- including vaccines, pharma products, medical devices, or other valuable shipment(s) with particular relevance into expanding B2B enterprise market use cases.

Thanks,

Elliot Klein
